ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I am satisfied with the quality of the program.
The program facilitators listened to what I was trying to get across.
My needs were met by the program.
The program facilitators explained everything clearly.
I would recommend the program to a friend.
The program facilitators were not negative or critical towards me.
I would attend more sessions of the  program if they were offered.
The program facilitators were warm and friendly towards me.
I am now able to deal more effectively with my problems
I felt free to express myself in the program.
I was able to focus on what was a real concern to me in the program.
The program facilitators seemed to understand what I was thinking and feeling.
How much did this treatment help with the specific problem that led you to therapy?
Notes: 1=Made things a lot better; 2=Made things somewhat better; 3=Made no difference; 4=Made things somewhat worse; 5=Made things a lot worse

ElementDescription: Patient's level of Satisfaction With Therapy (ST)
Notes: Sum the scores of all even number items (sttsr2, sttsr4, sttsr6, sttsr8, sttsr10, sttsr12)

ElementDescription: Patient's level of Satisfaction With Therapist (SWT)
Notes: Sum the scores of all odd number items (sttsr1, sttsr3, sttsr5, sttsr7, sttsr9, sttsr11)

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version
